narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Critical and formal readings of family photography, and bringing family photography into conversations and complications across racial, class, and gendered lines.
Wonderful and sensitive reading and of photography. Made me think about images in whole new way.

I enjoyed how heavily student driven and oriented this seminar was. I gained tremendous insight into the importance of the family photograph, elevating the ubiquitous to the surreal. The readings were interdisciplinary and applicable to all sorts of visual culture analysis.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: At times certain concepts and rhetoric seemed inaccessible but the professors facilitated great conversation.
Amazing reading and and image selections. I wish discussion had been more directed and that we had more time. The assignments were at times confusing and poorly explained.
